        <div class="image-column">
            <img src="img/photographer.jpg" alt="Birthday Photoshoot">
        </div>
        <div class="text-column">
            <h1>Capture the Moments</h1>
            <p>Birthday photography preserves the magic, emotion, and energy of the celebration. Whether it's a professional photographer or a skilled friend behind the camera, thoughtful planning ensures you’ll treasure those joyful moments forever.</p>

            <div class="advice-box">
                <h4 class="advice-title">Photography Tips from FIORE</h4>
                <p class="advice-content">Great photos come from great preparation. Here are some tips to make sure every smile, surprise, and candle-blowing moment is beautifully captured:</p>
                <ul class="bullet-list">
                    <li>Choose a photographer who understands your style—candid, posed, or a mix of both.</li>
                    <li>Scout locations in advance with good natural light or unique backdrops.</li>
                    <li>Capture details—decorations, cake close-ups, party favors, and table settings.</li>
                    <li>Plan key shots: blowing out candles, group photos, and special moments like speeches or dances.</li>
                    <li>Use props like balloons, confetti, or banners to enhance the fun vibe.</li>
                    <li>Have a mini shoot with the birthday person before guests arrive—less distraction, better lighting.</li>
                    <li>Ensure photos are backed up and shared with guests afterward for lasting memories.</li>
                </ul>
            </div><br>
